{"ts": "2026-04-24T02:21:21Z", "event": "clarify_critic", "feature": "ship-curl-sh-bootstrap-installer-for-cortex-command", "findings": ["Intent clarity rated HIGH ignores that the ticket body defers `cortex upgrade` semantics to '118's author'.", "Entry-point/final-step hedge in the ticket body ('`~/.cortex/bin/cortex setup` or whatever resolves') names a subcommand that does not exist in cli.py.", "Scope boundedness rated HIGH but hosting ('cortex.sh or GitHub Pages') and idempotence strategy are enumerated as requirements without definition.", "Out-of-scope list omits platform/shell coverage, existing `~/.cortex` handling, GPG/signature verification, and `curl | sh` security posture.", "Requirements alignment rated HIGH but hides the clone-behind-a-URL tension with project.md's 'clone or fork' framing.", "Branded hosted endpoint blurs the 'published package out of scope' line in project.md.", "Complexity may be understated given hosting + domain + CLI + bootstrap UX span.", "Criticality rated `high` underweights supply-chain blast radius of a hosted curl|sh endpoint."], "dispositions": {"apply": 3, "dismiss": 3, "ask": 2}, "applied_fixes": ["Added upgrade-semantics edge cases (dirty tree, detached HEAD, reinstall scope) to Open Questions for research.", "Changed Requirements Alignment from 'Aligned' to 'Partial alignment — DR-8 in epic research resolved the clone/fork tension and proposed a project.md update; this ticket proceeds against that resolution.'", "Self-resolved entry-point hedge: ticket body was updated to acknowledge 117 retirement-only state; post-install UX is Spec-phase Open Decision, not Clarify gap. Hosting URL self-resolved to GitHub raw URL per docs/setup.md. Platform self-resolved to macOS + Linux + WSL-transparent per README."], "dismissals": [{"finding_index": 5, "rationale": "Duplicate of finding 4 — same tension (hosted/branded distribution vs clone/fork), same DR-8 resolution applies."}, {"finding_index": 6, "rationale": "Lifecycle complexity tiers are binary (simple|complex) per clarify.md §5; `complex` is already the ceiling. Escalation beyond complex handled via criticality."}, {"finding_index": 3, "rationale": "Self-resolved: README explicitly targets macOS with Linux/Windows in docs/setup.md; primary maintainer is macOS; WSL handles Windows transparently via bash. Platform coverage is clear from project convention. GPG/signature verification and curl|sh security are valid concerns but belong in Spec-phase risk discussion, not Clarify blockers — prior art (rustup/nvm/uv) accepts the same posture."}], "status": "ok"}
